parameters:
Memimi: Hmm... I didn't know such a stylish bar had opened
in the underground city... A bar specializing in monsters,
that doesn't sound too noisy, which is nice. I guess I have
no choice but to make this my regular haunt...

Bunny-chan: Memimi-chan, over here, over here♪ The juice is
delicious!

Memimi: Ah, if it isn't Bunny-chan... Could you please not
call me by my real name outside...? And speaking of which,
your face...

Bunny-chan: Ehehe~ This visor is quite heavy. Right now,
it's just the manager here, so it's okay to show my face!
He's a trustworthy person, so it's totally okay even if he
knows our real names.

She is the monster known as Electro Rabbit, commonly
referred to as Bunny-chan. She's a notorious monster from
the dark organization who acts as a referee and manages the
progress of Monster Fights.

As a member of the Monster Fight management team, she
maintains neutrality during matches, but she and Memimi are
the same age and among the few female monsters, so
privately, they are good friends.

Memimi: No, no... For us monsters, having our identity
revealed is extremely dangerous... The manager you say...?
Hm? Hmmm!?

Brachiocondor: Guguge... Don't worry, I'll keep a fellow
monster's secret safe! Besides, I've had a long relationship
with Shark Broccoli. I've known about your true identity for
ages!

Memimi: Whoa, isn't that Brachiocondor!? Why are you
here...?

Brachiocondor: The match the other day was splendid! I've
been fighting since Monster Fight was established, and I
think it's about time for me to call it quits. I've retired
and decided to run this place.

Memimi: Is that so... I didn't know that... I'll bring a
potted plant next time. It was an honor to be your last
opponent.

Bunny-chan: It was a great match... I'm glad I got to see
that cross-counter finish up close♪

Brachiocondor: I'm confident in the taste, so make sure to
come by often! I've got to support my wife and two
daughters, so I'm going to work hard!!
Memimi: So you were married... huh.
'モンスター・ファイト試合会場に行こう！'

Brachiocondor: Shark Broccoli was a splendid villain... He
worried about the fate of the city that had become a lawless
dark zone, and he worked to persuade the influential
villains of that time to hold the Monster Fight!

Memimi: Amazing... As expected of our great leader-sama...!
That person is kinder than anyone else, with a heart as vast
as the ocean, enveloping all of us...!

Brachiocondor: Shark Broccoli and I, as the first generation
fighters of the Monster Fight, battled through many
fights... He retired before we could fight directly. I was
thinking of retiring too, whether I won or lost against his
beloved disciple whom he trained.

Memimi: Ugh... Waaah... Brachiocondor...! You, you are...!!
Brachiocondor---!!!
Bunny-chan: You two are really close, huh...

Brachiocondor: I've been exposed... Don't worry about it...
Battle is a matter of luck, sometimes you lose! It's not
about winning or losing, it's about whether you can keep
your spirit unbroken!

Memimi: Your consolation is heartwarming... As a senior in
monster fighting, you really say the right things,
Brachiocondor...

Brachiocondor: As a disciple of Shark Broccoli, you've got
some serious guts! To think someone would actually take on
that task with those rules... You're out of this world...

Memimi: As a high-ranking member of the organization, I have
to show some backbone too... Well, it was a bit tough, I
must admit... Just a bit though...

Brachiocondor: There's always someone you just can't beat,
no matter what. Even I have one, and so does Shark
Broccoli—a natural enemy. Fortunately, we've never had to
face each other in a match.

Memimi: Losing twice really gets me down... I'm not about to
give up, but thinking about the conditions for a rematch...
it's so daunting... *sigh*... my chest feels... ugh...

Brachiocondor: Honestly, I didn't think you had the guts to
make it through that brutal challenge and face a rematch
head-on. Your mental strength is way beyond Shark
Broccoli's...

Memimi: It's thanks to Shark Broccoli-sama, the great boss,
that I'm here... I will never break until I make his dream
come true. Even if it means embarrassing videos of me end up
on the net...

Brachiocondor: T-today, you can eat and drink anything for
free... yeah...

Bunny-chan: I get along well with Memimi-chan, but as a
person from the Monster Fight management, I'm completely
neutral! I won't show any bias in my judging, okay~?

Memimi: It goes without saying... Of course! Both Bunny-chan
and I, as members of the dark organization and as monsters,
must conduct ourselves with pride and dignity!

Bunny-chan: That's right, that's right! I'll be overseeing
the next match fairly too♪

Bunny-chan: We lost, huh... Hmm... Something feels off,
Anomalocaris Mosman-san... Maybe we should have an
investigation at the management headquarters...

Memimi: I appreciate the sentiment, but it's okay... It's
not necessary... Even if the opponent had resorted to
cowardly tactics, overcoming that is what makes a true
monster. It was my weakness that led to our defeat...

Bunny-chan: If Memimi-chan says so... Ah, but, you know...
about your outfit...

Memimi: This too must be a trial I have to accept as the
loser... Honestly, I'm embarrassed too, but I'll endure
it...

Bunny-chan: Ah, yeah... That's fine and all... but, um...
you might want to be careful with your chest area? If you're
not careful, it's kind of peeking out quite a bit...

Bunny-chan: Do your best in the rematch, Memimi-chan! ...I
wish you wouldn't push yourself too hard... As a girl,
that's just not okay...

Memimi: Ugh... I've caused you trouble too, Bunny-chan,
making you put up with perverted acts all day... I just
couldn't stand working under Anomalocaris Mosman...
Memimi: I just... I, I am...

Bunny-chan: Whoa, don't cry! Memimi-chaaan!! You're just
being too stubborn...

Bunny-chan: Things are getting worse and worse, Memimi-
chan... Of course, as a monster, I want you to do your
best... but as a friend, I think it would be better if you
quit being a monster... you're attending a good school after
all...

Memimi: Haha... I, originally, if not for Shark Broccoli-
sama picking me up, wouldn't even have a place to live, let
alone attend school... Quitting being a monster... that's
impossible...

Bunny-chan: Are you planning to fight again...? If so,
you'll be given another crazy condition...

Memimi: I'll do it... for the organization... I'll show
them... *mutter mutter*... ufufu...

Bunny-chan: I can't help you, and I have no choice but to
proceed as usual, right? Please don't be reckless... it's
bad for my heart...

Bunny-chan: Tonight is the rematch with Anomalocaris Mosman,
right, Memimi-chan♪ I'll do my best as the referee too, so
don't lose, okay? I'm neutral, but I'm cheering for you~.

Memimi: Thank you, Bunny-chan. Today, I will win for sure...
I'll remind those dark organization goons that there's a
Shark Duke in Nideki City!

Memimi: That's right... if I win, my reputation... will be
safe again... No more being looked at strangely by
everyone... No more rumors on the net or at school about my
genitals... ugh...

Memimi: ...fugu... ugh...! I am... I am still... ugh,
ughuu...

Bunny-chan: Aaah, calm down~...! You'll be fine, Memimi-
chan...! You can go back to your normal life again, so
please stop crying~!
